Aging Adults:

In adults, systolic blood pressure rises from early adulthood onward, up to at least age 70. The most practical and authoritative guide to ultrasound-guided nerve blocks. Downloaded by 200,000 medical professionals worldwide. Subscribe now to see why and:

- Instantly access all standardized nerve block techniques and management protocols that work
- Quickly navigate through the a comprehensive collection fo 60 NB techniques for head and neck, upper extremity, lower extremity, thoracic, and abdominal wall
- Instantly understand the principles of NBs
- Access amazing NYSORA’s anatomy, and reverse ultrasound anatomy illustrations and animations
- Learn best NBs choice for most common clinical indications
- Instantly recollect patient positioning, US landmarks, and logical step-by-step technique instructions
- Access clinical tips for every NB technique that make the outcome difference
- Access teaching collection of must-have for anatomy images, videos, and animations
- Complete information on practice of nerve blocks for exams-taking, including EDRA
- Build own regional anesthesia service using the APP template
- Access real-life clinical teaching videos
- Available in English and all other major languages (Spanish, French, German, Chinese, Dutch, Japanese, Portuguese)

Babylon gives you quick access to GPs, Physiotherapists, Nurses and Pharmacists—straight from your device. You can also take control of your wellbeing with digital health tools that are available 24/7.

HOW THE BABYLON APP WORKS
• Download the Babylon app for free
• Stay on top of your health 24/7 with our free digital health tools
• Book video or audio-only appointments with NHS clinicians at a time of your choice
• Prescribing clinicians can send an electronic prescription straight to the pharmacy of your choice

BABYLON GP AT HAND - GET FREE, 24/7 ACCESS TO NHS CLINICIANS
Book video appointments with a range of NHS clinicians, including GPs and physiotherapists. Appointments are free, available 24/7 and you can choose a time that suits you. In-person appointments are also available at our London and Birmingham clinics.**

Feeling off? Want to check your symptoms? Or find out how healthy you are? Our free digital health tools are here for you 24/7. Meet Symptom Checker and Healthcheck.

CHECK SYMPTOMS INSTANTLY
Answer questions about your symptoms and our AI-powered Symptom Checker can analyse your symptoms, potential causes and recommend possible next steps.

GET ACTIONABLE INSIGHTS FOR CURRENT AND FUTURE HEALTH
Try our Healthcheck tool to create a report of your overall current health. It can help identify risk factors and give you tips on how to stay healthy.

BUPA MEMBERS
If you have BUPA private medical insurance, you can speak to a clinician via the Babylon app for free. Just enter your BUPA membership code when registering.

WELLBEING 
Babylon Monitor helps you discover the impact of your habits on your health. You can use Babylon Monitor to sync your health data from your phone, wearables and apps—so everything’s in one place.

SAFETY
Your data is always safe. We’re regulated by the Care Quality Commission (CQC) for our doctor appointment services in the UK. Our clinicians are experienced and our doctors are GMC registered. We are compliant with ISO 27001 to protect all medical records and personal data.

Download the Babylon app for free and take control of your health. www.babylonhealth.com
Connect your existing health apps, such as HealthKit, to manage your health in one place.


*Healthcheck is currently unavailable for BUPA members.
**To register for GP at Hand, you will need to switch from your current GP practice. Once an application is made, a registration period will apply before you are able to access the service. Available for people living or working within the catchment area of one of our clinic locations. To book an in-person appointment, you must first have a digital appointment.
